verses.text_plain: And when the queen of Sheba heard of the fame of Solomon concerning the name of the Lord, she came to prove him with hard questions.
verses.verse_html: 1And when the queen of Sheba heard of the fame of Solomon concerning the name of the Lord, she came to prove him with hard questions.

verses.text_plain: And she came to Jerusalem with a very great train, with camels that bare spices, and very much gold, and precious stones: and when she was come to Solomon, she communed with him of all that was in her heart.
verses.verse_html: 2And she came to Jerusalem with a very great train, with camels that bare spices, and very much gold, and precious stones: and when she was come to Solomon, she communed with him of all that was in her heart.

tokens.text: with him of all that was in her heart

verses.text_plain: And Solomon told her all her questions: there was not any thing hid from the king, which he told her not.
verses.verse_html:
3And Solomon told her all her questions: there was not any thing hid from the king, which he told her not. ▼
▼ questions: Heb. words

verses.text_plain: And when the queen of Sheba had seen all Solomon’s wisdom, and the house that he had built,
verses.verse_html: 4And when the queen of Sheba had seen all Solomon’s wisdom, and the house that he had built,

verses.text_plain: And the meat of his table, and the sitting of his servants, and the attendance of his ministers, and their apparel, and his cupbearers, and his ascent by which he went up unto the house of the Lord; there was no more spirit in her.
verses.verse_html:
5And the meat of his table, and the sitting of his servants, and the attendance of his ministers, and their apparel, and his cupbearers, and his ascent by which he went up unto the house of the Lord; there was no more spirit in her. ▼
▼ attendance: Heb. standing
 , ▼
▼ cupbearers: or, butlers

verses.text_plain: And she said to the king, It was a true report that I heard in mine own land of thy acts and of thy wisdom.
verses.verse_html:
6And she said to the king, It was a true report that I heard in mine own land of thy acts and of thy wisdom. ▼
▼ report: Heb. word
 , ▼
▼ acts: or, sayings

verses.text_plain: Howbeit I believed not the words, until I came, and mine eyes had seen it: and, behold, the half was not told me: thy wisdom and prosperity exceedeth the fame which I heard.
verses.verse_html:
7Howbeit I believed not the words, until I came, and mine eyes had seen it: and, behold, the half was not told me: thy wisdom and prosperity exceedeth the fame which I heard. ▼
▼ thy…: Heb. thou hast added wisdom and goodness to

footnotes.body_text: ▼ thy…: Heb. thou hast added wisdom and goodness to
footnotes.body_html: ▼ thy…: Heb. thou hast added wisdom and goodness to

verses.text_plain: Happy are thy men, happy are these thy servants, which stand continually before thee, and that hear thy wisdom.
verses.verse_html: 8Happy are thy men, happy are these thy servants, which stand continually before thee, and that hear thy wisdom.

verses.text_plain: Blessed be the Lord thy God, which delighted in thee, to set thee on the throne of Israel: because the Lord loved Israel for ever, therefore made he thee king, to do judgment and justice.
verses.verse_html: 9Blessed be the Lord thy God, which delighted in thee, to set thee on the throne of Israel: because the Lord loved Israel for ever, therefore made he thee king, to do judgment and justice.

verses.text_plain: And she gave the king an hundred and twenty talents of gold, and of spices very great store, and precious stones: there came no more such abundance of spices as these which the queen of Sheba gave to king Solomon.
verses.verse_html: 10And she gave the king an hundred and twenty talents of gold, and of spices very great store, and precious stones: there came no more such abundance of spices as these which the queen of Sheba gave to king Solomon.

verses.text_plain: And the navy also of Hiram, that brought gold from Ophir, brought in from Ophir great plenty of almug trees, and precious stones.
verses.verse_html:
11And the navy also of Hiram, that brought gold from Ophir, brought in from Ophir great plenty of almug trees, and precious stones. ▼
▼ almug…: also called, algum trees

footnotes.body_html: ▼ almug…: also called, algum trees

verses.text_plain: And the king made of the almug trees pillars for the house of the Lord, and for the king’s house, harps also and psalteries for singers: there came no such almug trees, nor were seen unto this day.
verses.verse_html:
12And the king made of the almug trees pillars for the house of the Lord, and for the king’s house, harps also and psalteries for singers: there came no such almug trees, nor were seen unto this day. ▼
▼ pillars: or, rails: Heb. a prop

footnotes.body_text: ▼ pillars: or, rails: Heb. a prop
footnotes.body_html: ▼ pillars: or, rails: Heb. a prop

verses.text_plain: And king Solomon gave unto the queen of Sheba all her desire, whatsoever she asked, beside that which Solomon gave her of his royal bounty. So she turned and went to her own country, she and her servants.
verses.verse_html:
13And king Solomon gave unto the queen of Sheba all her desire, whatsoever she asked, beside that which Solomon gave her of his royal bounty. So she turned and went to her own country, she and her servants. ▼
▼ of his…: Heb. according to the hand of king Solomon

footnotes.body_text: ▼ of his…: Heb. according to the hand of king Solomon
footnotes.body_html: ▼ of his…: Heb. according to the hand of king Solomon

verses.text_plain: Now the weight of gold that came to Solomon in one year was six hundred threescore and six talents of gold,
verses.verse_html: 14Now the weight of gold that came to Solomon in one year was six hundred threescore and six talents of gold,

verses.text_plain: Beside that he had of the merchantmen, and of the traffick of the spice merchants, and of all the kings of Arabia, and of the governors of the country.
verses.verse_html:
15Beside that he had of the merchantmen, and of the traffick of the spice merchants, and of all the kings of Arabia, and of the governors of the country. ▼
▼ governors: or, captains

verses.text_plain: And king Solomon made two hundred targets of beaten gold: six hundred shekels of gold went to one target.
verses.verse_html: 16And king Solomon made two hundred targets of beaten gold: six hundred shekels of gold went to one target.

verses.text_plain: And he made three hundred shields of beaten gold; three pound of gold went to one shield: and the king put them in the house of the forest of Lebanon.
verses.verse_html: 17And he made three hundred shields of beaten gold; three pound of gold went to one shield: and the king put them in the house of the forest of Lebanon.

verses.text_plain: Moreover the king made a great throne of ivory, and overlaid it with the best gold.
verses.verse_html: 18Moreover the king made a great throne of ivory, and overlaid it with the best gold.

verses.text_plain: The throne had six steps, and the top of the throne was round behind: and there were stays on either side on the place of the seat, and two lions stood beside the stays.
verses.verse_html:
19The throne had six steps, and the top of the throne was round behind: and there were stays on either side on the place of the seat, and two lions stood beside the stays. ▼
▼ behind: Heb. on the hinder part thereof
 , ▼
▼ stays: Heb. hands

tokens.text: on either side on the place

footnotes.body_text: ▼ behind: Heb. on the hinder part thereof
footnotes.body_html: ▼ behind: Heb. on the hinder part thereof

verses.text_plain: And twelve lions stood there on the one side and on the other upon the six steps: there was not the like made in any kingdom.
verses.verse_html:
20And twelve lions stood there on the one side and on the other upon the six steps: there was not the like made in any kingdom. ▼
▼ the like: Heb. so

tokens.text: there on the one side and on the other upon the six

footnotes.body_html: ▼ the like: Heb. so

verses.text_plain: And all king Solomon’s drinking vessels were of gold, and all the vessels of the house of the forest of Lebanon were of pure gold; none were of silver: it was nothing accounted of in the days of Solomon.
verses.verse_html:
21And all king Solomon’s drinking vessels were of gold, and all the vessels of the house of the forest of Lebanon were of pure gold; none were of silver: it was nothing accounted of in the days of Solomon. ▼
▼ none…: or, there was no silver in them

footnotes.body_text: ▼ none…: or, there was no silver in them
footnotes.body_html: ▼ none…: or, there was no silver in them

verses.text_plain: For the king had at sea a navy of Tharshish with the navy of Hiram: once in three years came the navy of Tharshish, bringing gold, and silver, ivory, and apes, and peacocks.
verses.verse_html:
22For the king had at sea a navy of Tharshish with the navy of Hiram: once in three years came the navy of Tharshish, bringing gold, and silver, ivory, and apes, and peacocks. ▼
▼ ivory: or, elephants’ teeth

footnotes.body_html: ▼ ivory: or, elephants’ teeth

verses.text_plain: So king Solomon exceeded all the kings of the earth for riches and for wisdom.
verses.verse_html: 23So king Solomon exceeded all the kings of the earth for riches and for wisdom.

verses.text_plain: And all the earth sought to Solomon, to hear his wisdom, which God had put in his heart.
verses.verse_html:
24And all the earth sought to Solomon, to hear his wisdom, which God had put in his heart. ▼
▼ sought to: Heb. sought the face of

footnotes.body_text: ▼ sought to: Heb. sought the face of
footnotes.body_html: ▼ sought to: Heb. sought the face of

verses.text_plain: And they brought every man his present, vessels of silver, and vessels of gold, and garments, and armour, and spices, horses, and mules, a rate year by year.
verses.verse_html: 25And they brought every man his present, vessels of silver, and vessels of gold, and garments, and armour, and spices, horses, and mules, a rate year by year.

verses.text_plain: And Solomon gathered together chariots and horsemen: and he had a thousand and four hundred chariots, and twelve thousand horsemen, whom he bestowed in the cities for chariots, and with the king at Jerusalem.
verses.verse_html: 26And Solomon gathered together chariots and horsemen: and he had a thousand and four hundred chariots, and twelve thousand horsemen, whom he bestowed in the cities for chariots, and with the king at Jerusalem.

verses.text_plain: And the king made silver to be in Jerusalem as stones, and cedars made he to be as the sycomore trees that are in the vale, for abundance.
verses.verse_html:
27And the king made silver to be in Jerusalem as stones, and cedars made he to be as the sycomore trees that are in the vale, for abundance. ▼
▼ made: Heb. gave

verses.text_plain: And Solomon had horses brought out of Egypt, and linen yarn: the king’s merchants received the linen yarn at a price.
verses.verse_html:
28And Solomon had horses brought out of Egypt, and linen yarn: the king’s merchants received the linen yarn at a price. ▼
▼ And Solomon…: Heb. And the going forth of the horses which was Solomon’s

footnotes.body_text: ▼ And Solomon…: Heb. And the going forth of the horses which was Solomon’s
footnotes.body_html: ▼ And Solomon…: Heb. And the going forth of the horses which was Solomon’s

verses.text_plain: And a chariot came up and went out of Egypt for six hundred shekels of silver, and an horse for an hundred and fifty: and so for all the kings of the Hittites, and for the kings of Syria, did they bring them out by their means.
verses.verse_html:
29And a chariot came up and went out of Egypt for six hundred shekels of silver, and an horse for an hundred and fifty: and so for all the kings of the Hittites, and for the kings of Syria, did they bring them out by their means. ▼
▼ by their…: Heb. by their hand

tokens.text: and so for all the kings

footnotes.body_text: ▼ by their…: Heb. by their hand
footnotes.body_html: ▼ by their…: Heb. by their hand
